A ~15cm indoor car is great for a beginner project - manageable size, no weatherproofing needed.

Quick clarification:

Is your RC car currently remote-controlled (has its own controller/receiver)? We'll likely replace that brain with a microcontroller like an ESP32 that makes its own decisions.

For your beginner-friendly setup, I'm thinking:

ESP32
as the brain (~$8)
LD2410
mmWave radar for obstacle detection (~$6)
L298N
motor driver to control wheels (~$4)
Maybe 1-2 cheap
HC-SR04
ultrasonics for side awareness (~$2 each)
This keeps you well under budget with room for extras!

One more question: Do you want it to simply avoid obstacles (reactive), or actually navigate to a destination (like across a room)? The second is trickier but totally learnable!

